      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The primary reasons for the overrepresentation of certain racial groups in the US prison system are multifaceted and rooted in societal and historical factors. For African Americans, it's largely due to systemic racism, mass incarceration, and the War on Drugs, which have disproportionately targeted and punished Black communities. Additionally, poverty, lack of access to quality education and job opportunities, and the perpetuation of racial biases in law enforcement and the justice system all contribute to this disparity. Meanwhile, Hispanic and Native American populations are also disproportionately represented due to similar structural issues and historical trauma.",
